===Noun===
'''state''' (plural: [[states]])

#Any [[sovereign]] [[nation]].
#A political division that denotes a member of a [[federation]] that also retains a high degree of autonomy, even though it might technically be a part of another country.  A good example of this kind of state would be one of the 50 [[United States]].  Another term that is used for this kind of political entity is [[Province]].
#A condition (''example: a state of being'')

